abstract: The California senator has not always offered accurate defenses of her record or assessments of President Trump’s policies.
snippet: The California senator has not always offered accurate defenses of her record or assessments of President Trump’s policies.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris is aiming to reset her presidential campaign after a strong start and subsequent slump by highlighting her career as a glass-ceiling-shattering prosecutor and making the case against President Trump.

abstract: For years, repealing the measure was not part of the political conversation. But now, almost every Democratic presidential candidate is calling for it.
snippet: For years, repealing the measure was not part of the political conversation. But now, almost every Democratic presidential candidate is calling for it.
lead_paragraph: As a wave of highly restrictive state laws have made abortion a key issue in the 2020 campaign, the Hyde Amendment has drawn new scrutiny.

abstract: As Mayor Bill de Blasio forges ahead with his improbable presidential bid, endorsements seem hard to come by.
snippet: As Mayor Bill de Blasio forges ahead with his improbable presidential bid, endorsements seem hard to come by.
lead_paragraph: This week, Bill de Blasio’s presidential campaign, a project that has generated all the promise and enthusiasm of an afternoon in small-claims court, announced that its candidate had received his first endorsements. You might assume that those endorsements came from local elected officials, because that is so often the way of things. They did not. Beto O’Rourke, he of bass guitars and El Paso, has gained more support from New York congressional representatives in his own presidential bid than the mayor of New York City.

abstract: In the On Politics newsletter: Some of the former vice president’s positions seem more in line with the Democratic Party of 2007.

abstract: Nearly 100 Democratic members of Congress, including several presidential hopefuls, signed letters calling for an end to the State Department policy.
snippet: Nearly 100 Democratic members of Congress, including several presidential hopefuls, signed letters calling for an end to the State Department policy.
lead_paragraph: Nearly 20 Democratic senators and 80 members of the House of Representatives signed sharply worded letters that were sent to Secretary of State Mike Pompeo on Thursday, calling on his department to reverse a policy that has been used to deny citizenship to children of Americans born abroad through assisted reproductive technology.

headline_main: Democrats Urge Pompeo to End Policy Used to Deny Citizenship to Children of Gay Couples

abstract: Until recently big tech companies were seen as one of the few relatively untainted sources of big-money donations for Democrats. Now, that’s changing.
snippet: Until recently big tech companies were seen as one of the few relatively untainted sources of big-money donations for Democrats. Now, that’s changing.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Top Democrats in Washington and on the 2020 campaign trail are taking technology giants to task, calling them too big, too powerful and too careless about privacy. “The era of self-regulation is over,” Speaker Nancy Pelosi declared on Monday.

abstract: Reginald Hudlin’s documentary about Clarence Avant includes many golden anecdotes.
snippet: Reginald Hudlin’s documentary about Clarence Avant includes many golden anecdotes.
lead_paragraph: It’s not often that a documentary features testimonials from two former presidents (Clinton and Obama) and a current presidential candidate (Kamala Harris), but that’s the case with “The Black Godfather,” a tribute to Clarence Avant.

abstract: Other candidates should expand her plan to prevent bad laws from going into effect.
snippet: Other candidates should expand her plan to prevent bad laws from going into effect.
lead_paragraph: We need more ideas like the one Senator Kamala Harris of California proposed last week to stop abortion laws from going into effect unless the federal government agrees they comply with Roe v. Wade.

abstract: The retired senator Mike Gravel gave two young fans his Twitter password and permission to campaign in his name. It might be a stunt — or the future of politics.
snippet: The retired senator Mike Gravel gave two young fans his Twitter password and permission to campaign in his name. It might be a stunt — or the future of politics.
lead_paragraph: Zach Montellaro, a Politico reporter, reads the Federal Election Commission website like a tabloid. He not only trawls the big, dry database in which presidential candidates register to run; he also reads several smaller aftermarket ones that reformat the filings from the first. On Twitter, he follows F.E.C. bots that tweet out campaign filings as they post. On the night of March 19, he was up late when one such tweet, from @CATargetBot, crossed his feed: “NEW FEC F1 #POTUS Mike Gravel for President Exploratory Committee.”

abstract: Joe Biden faced a backlash over his support for the measure, which advocates say disproportionately harms poor women and women of color.
snippet: Joe Biden faced a backlash over his support for the measure, which advocates say disproportionately harms poor women and women of color.
lead_paragraph: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., who has shunned today’s Democratic Party orthodoxy on issues from crime to compromising with Republicans, again broke with his party’s base and many of his campaign rivals on Wednesday when his campaign confirmed that he still backs the Hyde Amendment, a measure that prohibits the use of federal funds for abortion with exceptions for cases involving rape, incest and when the life of the mother is in danger.
